ss=m><span class=title>   Re: Problems in HoT</span><hr size=1> I am not one to typically support the Large guilds, but in this case, I sorta do.  When only 2 (or perhaps 3) guilds are able to kill a certain creature, then a &quot;Gentlemen's Agreement&quot; seems adequate.  Really, only they know what is involved in killing the creature (and his cohorts, if any).  This also has the perk of letting them work out the nuances of this particular rotation quietly and thoroughly.<br>
<br>
It is the responsibility of the 2 or 3 large guilds to be continually looking behind them for those other guilds that may be ready, or close to ready, to enter the rotation.<br>
<br>
Once more than those 2 or 3 guilds start nearing the capability of killing those same creatures, then the agreement needs to be brought to ALL member guilds of the RTA to discuss and vote.  The best place to begin the discussion is with the then standing &quot;Gentlemen's Agreement.&quot;<br>
<br>
