I really don't think the guilds on rotation have the right to make rules as they go without the vote of the community.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Uh, yeah, actually, they do have the right. <br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but quite frankly, a guild like, to use an old example, United Necros, has no business telling Clan Bashemded what to do on a rotation with Zlandicar, because they are not on it with us. In the same respect, Clan Bashemded has no right to say to BotS &quot;Hey, guys, you know Vex Thal? Here are the rules for it, as I see it. Pay attention&quot;. <br>
<br>
To hell with that. If you can't actually kill the big mobs in question, why should you get a say about how it is run? If you want to change it once you get there, and prove you can do it, talk to the guilds on the rotation with you. If your suggestion is a good one, they'll listen. If it's self serving and bad, then they won't. The point is, until you are actually able to kill it, it doesn't mean anything to you, except conjecture and arrogence. <br>
<br>
Does it not occur to anyone that if two guilds are after one mob, and a rotation is made, it's not going to be a weighted rotation. There will never be a stipulation on any mob that says &quot;yeah, you can kill it when you wait your turn, but the key parts have to be given to members of another guild&quot; because no one is stupid enough to enter into that agreement. <br>
<br>
Here's the biggest thing to remember about rotations: They are voluntary! If they were not at least TRYING to be fair, people would abandon them and go FFA on the mob in question. So yes, the guilds on a rotation, and *only* those guilds have the ability to decide what happens with those mobs. <br>
<br>
Quite frankly, asking my opinion on ToVN rotations is more than useless, because I don't know how it works first hand, and as such, can add only conjecture and random garbage to the discussion, thus making it worse. <br>
<br>
If you 'know all about killing the mobs' then prove it: go kill them, get on the rotation, get your say. <br>
<br>
Basically all the rotations will come down to this: <br>
<br>
Kill the mobs within 24 hours, or pass to the next guild in line so that they can kill the mobs. (noted exception of ToVN with 48 hours and delay to be sure all mobs are up). <br>
<br>
Where is the imput of the entire community required?<br>
<br>
That's right... it's not. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
<br>
<br>
